{
  "id": "2021-03-25_screen_english",
  "date": "2021-03-25",
  "corner": "screen_english",
  "corner_label": "Screen English",
  "title": "I have nowhere else to go",
  "movie": "",
  "duration_sec": 618.3,
  "audio_url": "https://rtyzdyyfahddqshgyjvn.supabase.co/storage/v1/object/public/gmp-audio/2021-03-25_screen_english.mp3",
  "script": [
    {
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 1.0,
      "text": "스크린 잉글리쉬"
    },
    {
      "start": 1.0,
      "end": 20.76,
      "text": "The best way to enjoy a movie."
    },
    {
      "start": 21.1,
      "end": 22.58,
      "text": "스크린 잉글리쉬 타임."
    },
    {
      "start": 22.96,
      "end": 26.1,
      "text": "3월에 함께하고 있는 영화는 어디갔어 버나데드"
    },
    {
      "start": 26.1,
      "end": 27.0,
      "text": "Where do you go?"
    },
    {
      "start": 27.18,
      "end": 27.9,
      "text": "버나데드"
    },
    {
      "start": 27.9,
      "end": 30.04,
      "text": "그렇죠? 바로 이 영화입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 30.1,
      "end": 34.1,
      "text": "8509님께서 크리스님 발음 굿"
    },
    {
      "start": 34.1,
      "end": 39.84,
      "text": "모든 외국인분들이 크리스님처럼 발음하시면 영어 배우기 편할텐데 라고 하셨어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 40.36,
      "end": 41.44,
      "text": "와우, what a compliment."
    },
    {
      "start": 41.74,
      "end": 42.08,
      "text": "그쵸."
    },
    {
      "start": 42.12,
      "end": 43.16,
      "text": "아주 극찬의 말씀입니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 43.16,
      "end": 47.6,
      "text": "아우, 역시 우리 크리스씨. 제가 다 자랑스러워집니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 47.7,
      "end": 49.5,
      "text": "막 자부심이 뿜뿜하고 있어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 49.56,
      "end": 49.96,
      "text": "아, 그래요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 50.12,
      "end": 50.34,
      "text": "네."
    },
    {
      "start": 50.6,
      "end": 51.34,
      "text": "아, thank you."
    },
    {
      "start": 51.42,
      "end": 53.54,
      "text": "네, 팔이 이렇게 안으로 굽는 게 맞는가봐요."
    },
    {
      "start": 54.74,
      "end": 56.36,
      "text": "자, 이제 시작을 해볼게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 57.14,
      "end": 58.84,
      "text": "주인공에 대해서 생각을 해보면"
    },
    {
      "start": 58.84,
      "end": 60.5,
      "text": "On one hand, I can say"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.5,
      "end": 62.14,
      "text": "Bernadette Fox has it all."
    },
    {
      "start": 62.68,
      "end": 63.58,
      "text": "Everything, 그쵸?"
    },
    {
      "start": 63.7,
      "end": 66.02,
      "text": "She does have a loving husband, LG,"
    },
    {
      "start": 66.32,
      "end": 68.14,
      "text": "and a brilliant daughter."
    },
    {
      "start": 68.38,
      "end": 69.86,
      "text": "But there's one thing missing."
    },
    {
      "start": 70.42,
      "end": 71.68,
      "text": "That is her."
    },
    {
      "start": 72.38,
      "end": 72.86,
      "text": "Herself."
    },
    {
      "start": 72.86,
      "end": 73.46,
      "text": "Herself."
    },
    {
      "start": 73.62,
      "end": 73.74,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 73.94,
      "end": 74.72,
      "text": "She doesn't know herself."
    },
    {
      "start": 74.92,
      "end": 75.22,
      "text": "맞아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 75.78,
      "end": 77.2,
      "text": "어느 순간, who am I?"
    },
    {
      "start": 77.42,
      "end": 78.28,
      "text": "Where am I?"
    },
    {
      "start": 78.38,
      "end": 80.14,
      "text": "이런 질문을 하게 되는 때가 있잖아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 80.36,
      "end": 81.16,
      "text": "Do you have those times?"
    },
    {
      "start": 81.4,
      "end": 81.8,
      "text": "저요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 82.04,
      "end": 84.12,
      "text": "When you get up and look in the mirror in the morning."
    },
    {
      "start": 84.28,
      "end": 85.12,
      "text": "What am I doing?"
    },
    {
      "start": 85.6,
      "end": 87.02,
      "text": "가끔 그럴 때 있는 것 같아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 87.48,
      "end": 89.5,
      "text": "언제라고 딱 꼬집어 이야기할 수는 없지만"
    },
    {
      "start": 89.5,
      "end": 90.96,
      "text": "있었던 적이 있었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 91.96,
      "end": 94.4,
      "text": "공허함도 느끼게 되는 순간이 있죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 94.9,
      "end": 95.42,
      "text": "인간인지라."
    },
    {
      "start": 95.86,
      "end": 97.28,
      "text": "그런데, fortunately,"
    },
    {
      "start": 97.86,
      "end": 100.18,
      "text": "Bernadette found herself again in Antarctica."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.18,
      "end": 100.82,
      "text": "Yes."
    },
    {
      "start": 100.98,
      "end": 101.22,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 101.54,
      "end": 103.84,
      "text": "She did go to Antarctica by herself."
    },
    {
      "start": 104.52,
      "end": 106.28,
      "text": "And she went to find herself."
    },
    {
      "start": 106.76,
      "end": 108.6,
      "text": "And she became creative again."
    },
    {
      "start": 108.74,
      "end": 109.08,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 109.24,
      "end": 111.38,
      "text": "She found another architectural project"
    },
    {
      "start": 111.38,
      "end": 112.6,
      "text": "and started working."
    },
    {
      "start": 112.86,
      "end": 114.04,
      "text": "And she was so happy."
    },
    {
      "start": 114.2,
      "end": 114.46,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 114.46,
      "end": 118.14,
      "text": "그러면 크리스 씨는 가고 싶은 여행지가 있어요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 118.24,
      "end": 118.76,
      "text": "막연함에?"
    },
    {
      "start": 119.36,
      "end": 120.28,
      "text": "막연하게나마?"
    },
    {
      "start": 120.58,
      "end": 122.42,
      "text": "아, 막연하게나마?"
    },
    {
      "start": 122.5,
      "end": 123.06,
      "text": "네, 네, 네."
    },
    {
      "start": 123.1,
      "end": 124.22,
      "text": "Just for fun."
    },
    {
      "start": 124.38,
      "end": 125.32,
      "text": "그냥 만약에."
    },
    {
      "start": 125.38,
      "end": 126.84,
      "text": "If I could go by myself."
    },
    {
      "start": 126.94,
      "end": 128.06,
      "text": "Just leave my family?"
    },
    {
      "start": 128.66,
      "end": 129.18,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 129.38,
      "end": 130.14,
      "text": "Go all by myself?"
    },
    {
      "start": 130.9,
      "end": 131.38,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 131.54,
      "end": 131.78,
      "text": "Wow."
    },
    {
      "start": 132.14,
      "end": 132.82,
      "text": "너무 좋아하는 거 아니에요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 133.02,
      "end": 134.02,
      "text": "That makes me excited."
    },
    {
      "start": 134.12,
      "end": 135.14,
      "text": "Just thinking about that."
    },
    {
      "start": 135.22,
      "end": 136.02,
      "text": "Where would I go?"
    },
    {
      "start": 136.34,
      "end": 137.26,
      "text": "I would probably,"
    },
    {
      "start": 137.38,
      "end": 138.36,
      "text": "well, to find myself"
    },
    {
      "start": 138.36,
      "end": 140.38,
      "text": "in a philosophical way,"
    },
    {
      "start": 140.38,
      "end": 142.5,
      "text": "I would probably go back home"
    },
    {
      "start": 142.5,
      "end": 144.56,
      "text": "or back to my original country,"
    },
    {
      "start": 144.96,
      "end": 145.54,
      "text": "the USA,"
    },
    {
      "start": 145.78,
      "end": 148.64,
      "text": "because you can find yourself at home"
    },
    {
      "start": 148.64,
      "end": 150.42,
      "text": "and I would probably"
    },
    {
      "start": 150.42,
      "end": 152.98,
      "text": "take a long cross-country trip"
    },
    {
      "start": 152.98,
      "end": 156.22,
      "text": "and meet family and friends on the way"
    },
    {
      "start": 156.22,
      "end": 158.02,
      "text": "or just take them with me"
    },
    {
      "start": 158.02,
      "end": 160.88,
      "text": "and walk and drive and hitchhike"
    },
    {
      "start": 160.88,
      "end": 162.9,
      "text": "and take many forms of transportation."
    },
    {
      "start": 163.28,
      "end": 166.68,
      "text": "와, 정말 다양한 일들을 할 수 있겠네요."
    },
    {
      "start": 167.18,
      "end": 169.12,
      "text": "미국이 워낙 넓으니까, 그렇죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 169.12,
      "end": 170.84,
      "text": "Cross the country 하려면"
    },
    {
      "start": 170.84,
      "end": 171.96,
      "text": "정말 오래 걸리겠어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 172.02,
      "end": 173.78,
      "text": "I'm going to need at least a year."
    },
    {
      "start": 174.32,
      "end": 175.3,
      "text": "I'm going to take a year off."
    },
    {
      "start": 175.38,
      "end": 175.62,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 176.02,
      "end": 176.82,
      "text": "완전 넓으니까."
    },
    {
      "start": 176.84,
      "end": 176.92,
      "text": "아, no, no."
    },
    {
      "start": 177.1,
      "end": 178.04,
      "text": "Family 파괴되니까."
    },
    {
      "start": 178.26,
      "end": 179.4,
      "text": "네, 안 가실 거죠?"
    },
    {
      "start": 179.56,
      "end": 180.0,
      "text": "Two weeks."
    },
    {
      "start": 181.36,
      "end": 181.92,
      "text": "좋아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 182.14,
      "end": 182.6,
      "text": "못 가요."
    },
    {
      "start": 182.76,
      "end": 183.54,
      "text": "아, 참."
    },
    {
      "start": 183.64,
      "end": 184.72,
      "text": "오늘 내용 듣고 오겠습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 185.4,
      "end": 187.61,
      "text": "Everything's so screwed up."
    },
    {
      "start": 188.27,
      "end": 191.23,
      "text": "I am really, really sorry"
    },
    {
      "start": 191.23,
      "end": 193.55,
      "text": "about your house"
    },
    {
      "start": 193.55,
      "end": 195.68,
      "text": "and the sign."
    },
    {
      "start": 197.01,
      "end": 197.61,
      "text": "Don't worry."
    },
    {
      "start": 198.03,
      "end": 199.21,
      "text": "Nobody will look for me here."
    },
    {
      "start": 200.56,
      "end": 201.8,
      "text": "Look, I know I'm not your friend."
    },
    {
      "start": 202.28,
      "end": 203.06,
      "text": "I'm nobody's friend."
    },
    {
      "start": 203.16,
      "end": 203.78,
      "text": "Let's face it."
    },
    {
      "start": 204.28,
      "end": 206.58,
      "text": "But when I was running from my house,"
    },
    {
      "start": 206.64,
      "end": 208.64,
      "text": "I thought maybe I could come here."
    },
    {
      "start": 209.57,
      "end": 210.61,
      "text": "I have nowhere else to go."
    },
    {
      "start": 211.27,
      "end": 213.41,
      "text": "I don't know anyone in Seattle."
    },
    {
      "start": 213.41,
      "end": 217.1,
      "text": "네, 오늘은 가슴이 찡해지는 장면이었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 217.7,
      "end": 221.02,
      "text": "She left her house through the bathroom's window."
    },
    {
      "start": 221.14,
      "end": 223.22,
      "text": "She escaped through the bathroom window."
    },
    {
      "start": 223.28,
      "end": 223.58,
      "text": "Yeah."
    },
    {
      "start": 223.68,
      "end": 224.54,
      "text": "I need to go to the bathroom."
    },
    {
      "start": 224.84,
      "end": 225.96,
      "text": "She never came back."
    },
    {
      "start": 226.02,
      "end": 226.26,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 227.26,
      "end": 228.98,
      "text": "화장실에 있는 창문을 통해서"
    },
    {
      "start": 228.98,
      "end": 232.04,
      "text": "이웃집 오드리네 집에 가가지고"
    },
    {
      "start": 232.04,
      "end": 233.28,
      "text": "문을 두드리고"
    },
    {
      "start": 233.28,
      "end": 236.76,
      "text": "또 지금 숨겨달라고 부탁하는 장면이었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 236.76,
      "end": 237.68,
      "text": "And who is Audrey?"
    },
    {
      "start": 238.08,
      "end": 239.58,
      "text": "Audrey is that neighbor."
    },
    {
      "start": 239.78,
      "end": 241.12,
      "text": "That neighbor who"
    },
    {
      "start": 241.12,
      "end": 243.22,
      "text": "K-Pol 사건 당했던"
    },
    {
      "start": 243.22,
      "end": 244.56,
      "text": "That neighbor,"
    },
    {
      "start": 244.72,
      "end": 246.28,
      "text": "they are enemies."
    },
    {
      "start": 246.28,
      "end": 246.6,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 247.16,
      "end": 248.68,
      "text": "분명 평소에는"
    },
    {
      "start": 248.68,
      "end": 250.0,
      "text": "enemy였단 말이죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 250.42,
      "end": 251.14,
      "text": "근데 지금은"
    },
    {
      "start": 251.14,
      "end": 253.22,
      "text": "이렇게 도움을 구하고 있어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 253.58,
      "end": 254.54,
      "text": "이런 거 보면"
    },
    {
      "start": 254.54,
      "end": 258.36,
      "text": "완전 나쁜 적은 없는 것 같다라는 생각도 듭니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 258.46,
      "end": 259.42,
      "text": "That's a good point."
    },
    {
      "start": 259.64,
      "end": 259.68,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 259.68,
      "end": 261.5,
      "text": "Sometimes you need your enemies."
    },
    {
      "start": 261.78,
      "end": 263.9,
      "text": "Sometimes your enemies can be your friends."
    },
    {
      "start": 264.02,
      "end": 265.38,
      "text": "Depending on the situation."
    },
    {
      "start": 265.58,
      "end": 265.68,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 266.08,
      "end": 269.4,
      "text": "충분히 회복될 수 있는 상황들이 있는 것 같아요."
    },
    {
      "start": 269.9,
      "end": 271.38,
      "text": "자, 어떤 표현들이 있었나요?"
    },
    {
      "start": 271.72,
      "end": 272.48,
      "text": "Screwed up!"
    },
    {
      "start": 272.7,
      "end": 273.76,
      "text": "아, screwed up."
    },
    {
      "start": 273.78,
      "end": 274.82,
      "text": "This is a common expression."
    },
    {
      "start": 275.02,
      "end": 275.1,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 275.24,
      "end": 276.02,
      "text": "I screwed up."
    },
    {
      "start": 276.86,
      "end": 279.92,
      "text": "망쳤다, 엉망이 됐다 라는 의미였어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 280.68,
      "end": 281.8,
      "text": "Let's face it."
    },
    {
      "start": 281.98,
      "end": 283.92,
      "text": "페이스가 여기서는 동사로 쓰인 거죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 284.06,
      "end": 284.92,
      "text": "This is a good one too."
    },
    {
      "start": 285.04,
      "end": 285.3,
      "text": "그렇죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 285.96,
      "end": 288.78,
      "text": "직면하다라는 페이스라는 동사가 쓰였습니다."
    },
    {
      "start": 288.78,
      "end": 290.08,
      "text": "Let's face it."
    },
    {
      "start": 290.58,
      "end": 292.86,
      "text": "그것에 직면합시다 라는 거니까"
    },
    {
      "start": 292.86,
      "end": 294.1,
      "text": "뭐 인정할게요."
    },
    {
      "start": 294.6,
      "end": 297.04,
      "text": "아니면 frankly를 대신해서 쓸 수 있죠."
    },
    {
      "start": 297.2,
      "end": 298.04,
      "text": "아, 솔까말로."
    },
    {
      "start": 298.22,
      "end": 299.36,
      "text": "솔직하게 말하자."
    },
    {
      "start": 299.38,
      "end": 300.08,
      "text": "깜짝아."
    },
    {
      "start": 300.72,
      "end": 301.78,
      "text": "예상치 못한 표현이었어요."
    },
    {
      "start": 302.42,
      "end": 303.18,
      "text": "그 말이에요."
    },
    {
      "start": 303.28,
      "end": 304.16,
      "text": "Hey, let's face it."
    },
    {
      "start": 304.24,
      "end": 304.62,
      "text": "아, 네."
    },
    {
      "start": 305.46,
      "end": 307.1,
      "text": "제가 유행어를 더 모르는 것 같아요."
    },
    {
